{% extends 'check.j2' %}

{% block scope %}
- `{{ vars.skill_dir }}/SKILL.md` (frontmatter + structure)
- All `{{ vars.skill_dir }}/references/*.md` files
{% endblock %}

{% block rules %}
Read the conventions reference at
`{{ vars.reference_path }}`. Apply each rule to the skill.

The reference covers general authoring rules: frontmatter shape,
naming, description triggers, prose width, list formatting,
table formatting, file lengths, completion table, RFC 2119
keywords, handle policy, analytics logging, script discovery.

Look for violations the automated lint cannot catch — this
includes semantic judgments (rule applies despite surface text
matching, or rule does not apply despite surface text mismatch).

Ultrathink each rule before deciding whether it is violated.
{% endblock %}
